{"id":12498,"date":"2022-10-18T01:03:13","date_gmt":"2022-10-18T01:03:13","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=12498"},"modified":"2022-10-18T01:04:55","modified_gmt":"2022-10-18T01:04:55","slug":"queer-mobilizations-to-counter-monkeypox","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/queer-mobilizations-to-counter-monkeypox\/","title":{"rendered":"Queer Mobilizations To Counter Monkeypox"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-1 wp-block-column\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">How about:<br><br>LGBTQ+ folks mobilized &amp; demanded help<br><br>We didn\u2019t sit around waiting for the government to get its shit together. We organized vaxx events at our *bars*, we told our friends, many abstained from sex while waiting to get vaxxed<br><br>Just like we had to do in the 80s &amp; 90s <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/19B7csXbHA\">pic.twitter.com\/19B7csXbHA<\/a><\/p>&mdash; 5, 6, grab your Cruzifix ?\ufe0f\u200d? (@KirkCruz) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/KirkCruz\/status\/1570482485179326465?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">September 15, 2022<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-2 wp-block-column\">\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">The &quot;inexplicable&quot; decrease in monkeypox cases really makes you wonder how covid could have gone had we handed the response plan over to harm reduction queers<\/p>&mdash; Kim Tran (@but_im_kim_tran) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/but_im_kim_tran\/status\/1572380109893697539?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">September 21, 2022<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>As fears of Monkeypox spread arose in the spring and summer of 2022\u2014particularly in and around communities of men who have sex with men and their sexual partners\u2014many were concerned about the possibility of yet another overlapping pandemic, especially one that might further stigmatize LGBTQ populations at a time when they were facing increasing political attacks from the right. However, many queer, disability, and public health activists (and especially those at the intersection) quickly responded, demanding government action to equitably make vaccines available, particularly to communities most at-risk. Still, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/health\/health-news\/went-wrong-rollout-monkeypox-vaccine-rcna38017\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">government rollout was slow<\/a>, with resources for testing, vaccines, and treatments taking months to reach impacted communities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In September 2022, Wired magazine published an article with the headline, &#8220;Monkeypox Cases in the US Are Falling. No One Knows Why.&#8221; A number of activists highlighted the ways that queer communities responded to Monkeypox outbreaks (and government inaction) with urgency and community care, particularly citing queer responses to HIV\/AIDS\u2014such as the tweets above. Unsurprisingly, such general claims both quickly spread on social media and were also met with <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/reluctantlyjoe\/status\/1572617222388084738\" target=\"_blank\">critiques from within queer communities<\/a>, particularly drawing attention to the complications of HIV\/AIDS activism (and discourses of similarity across pandemics) as well as highlighting many queer activists&#8217; roles in Covid-19 response as well. \u2014Harris Kornstein<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>As fears of Monkeypox spread arose in the spring and summer of 2022\u2014particularly in and around communities of men who have sex with men and their sexual partners\u2014many were concerned about the possibility of yet another overlapping pandemic, especially one that might further stigmatize LGBTQ populations at a time when&hellip; <a class=\"continue\" href=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/queer-mobilizations-to-counter-monkeypox\/\">Continue Reading<span> Queer Mobilizations To Counter Monkeypox<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":12499,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"advanced_seo_description":"","jetpack_seo_html_title":"","jetpack_seo_noindex":false,"_FSMCFIC_featured_image_caption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_nocaption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_hide":""},"categories":[44],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Twitter-monkeypox.jpg?fit=1188%2C724&ssl=1","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/12498"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=12498"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/12498\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":12502,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/12498\/revisions\/12502"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/12499"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=12498"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=12498"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=12498"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}